Camm,

I've found another common lisp bug in gcl-2.5.2. 
To illustrate:

GCL-2.4> (setq a '(+))
GCL-2.4> (elt a 1)

Error: The index, 1, is too large

GCL-2.5.2> (setq a '(+))
GCL-2.5.2> (elt a 1)

Error: 1 is not of type POSITIVE-FIXNUM

Tim Daly
daly@idsi.net
axiom@tenkan.org



